@carryxyh Thank you for your information that I did not find anywhere on internet about the streaming incompatibility of dubbo protocol. 
Our question is apart from the RMI protocol, is there any other protocol (e.g., http) that supports stream?
We would like to not use RMI protocol since it will lead to the port randomness nature of JAVA RMI protocol that will clearly not work with system firewall.
